verbose_text: Since the enriched G-3 genes were expected to regulate the expression of the G-4 genes, we examined the interactions between 35 G-3 and 32 G-4 genes using IPA, and found that Agt interacted not only with Agtrap expressed in the rats at 3 and 6 weeks of age, but also indirectly interacted with Zbtb16 expressed in the rats at 6 weeks of age (XREF_FIG).
